  21. ‌let print_reg b f r =
  22.   Buffer.add_char b '%';
  23.   Buffer.add_string b (f r)

  25. ‌let opt_displ b displ =
  26.   if displ = 0 then ()
  27.   else if displ > 0 then bprintf b "+%d" displ
  28.   else bprintf b "%d" displ

  30. ‌let arg_mem b {arch; typ=_; idx; scale; base; sym; displ} =
  31. ‌  let string_of_register =
  32.     match arch with
  33.     | X86 -> string_of_reg32
  34.     | X64 -> string_of_reg64
  35.   in
  36.   begin match sym with
  37.   | None ->
  38.       if displ <> 0 || scale = 0 then
  39.         Buffer.add_string b (Int.to_string displ)
  40.   | Some s ->
  41.       Buffer.add_string b s;
  42.       opt_displ b displ
  43.   end;
  44.   if scale <> 0 then begin
  45.     Buffer.add_char b '(';
  46.     begin match base with
  47.     | None -> ()
  48.     | Some base -> print_reg b string_of_register base
  49.     end;
  50.     if base != None || scale <> 1 then Buffer.add_char b ',';
  51.     print_reg b string_of_register idx;
  52.     if scale <> 1 then bprintf b ",%s" (Int.to_string scale);
  53.     Buffer.add_char b ')'
  54.   end

  56. ‌let arg b = function
  57.   | Sym x -> Buffer.add_char b '$'; Buffer.add_string b x
  58.   | Imm x -> bprintf b "$%Ld" x
  59.   | Reg8L x -> print_reg b string_of_reg8l x
  60.   | Reg8H x -> print_reg b string_of_reg8h x
  61.   | Reg16 x -> print_reg b string_of_reg16 x
  62.   | Reg32 x -> print_reg b string_of_reg32 x
  63.   | Reg64 x -> print_reg b string_of_reg64 x
  64.   | Regf x  -> print_reg b string_of_registerf x
  65.   | Mem addr -> arg_mem b addr
  66.   | Mem64_RIP (_, s, displ) -> bprintf b "%s%a(%%rip)" s opt_displ displ

  68. ‌let rec cst b = function
  69.   | ConstLabel _ | Const _ | ConstThis as c -> scst b c
  70.   | ConstAdd (c1, c2) -> bprintf b "%a + %a" scst c1 scst c2
  71.   | ConstSub (c1, c2) -> bprintf b "%a - %a" scst c1 scst c2

  73. and scst b = function
  74.   | ConstThis -> Buffer.add_string b "."
  75.   | ConstLabel l -> Buffer.add_string b l
  76.   | Const n when n <= 0x7FFF_FFFFL && n >= -0x8000_0000L ->
  77.       Buffer.add_string b (Int64.to_string n)
  78.   | Const n -> bprintf b "0x%Lx" n
  79.   | ConstAdd (c1, c2) -> bprintf b "(%a + %a)" scst c1 scst c2
  80.   | ConstSub (c1, c2) -> bprintf b "(%a - %a)" scst c1 scst c2

  82. ‌let typeof = function
  83.   | Mem {typ; _} | Mem64_RIP (typ, _, _) -> typ
  84.   | Reg8L _ | Reg8H _ -> BYTE
  85.   | Reg16 _ -> WORD
  86.   | Reg32 _ -> DWORD
  87.   | Reg64 _ -> QWORD
  88.   | Imm _ | Sym _ -> NONE
  89.   | Regf _ -> assert false

  91. ‌let suf arg =
  92.   match typeof arg with
  93.   | BYTE -> "b"
  94.   | WORD -> "w"
  95.   | DWORD | REAL8 -> "l"
  96.   | QWORD -> "q"
  97.   | REAL4 -> "s"
  98.   | NONE -> ""
  99.   | OWORD | NEAR | PROC -> assert false

  101. ‌let i0 b s = bprintf b "\t%s" s
  102. ‌let i1 b s x = bprintf b "\t%s\t%a" s arg x
  103. ‌let i1_s b s x = bprintf b "\t%s%s\t%a" s (suf x) arg x
  104. ‌let i2 b s x y = bprintf b "\t%s\t%a, %a" s arg x arg y
  105. ‌let i2_s b s x y = bprintf b "\t%s%s\t%a, %a" s (suf y) arg x arg y
  106. ‌let i2_ss b s x y = bprintf b "\t%s%s%s\t%a, %a" s (suf x) (suf y) arg x arg y

  108. ‌let i1_call_jmp b s = function
  109.   (* this is the encoding of jump labels: don't use * *)
  110.   | Mem {arch=X86; idx=_;   scale=0; base=None; sym=Some _; _} as x ->
  111.       i1 b s x
  112.   | Reg32 _ | Reg64 _ | Mem _  | Mem64_RIP _ as x ->
  113.       bprintf b "\t%s\t*%a" s arg x
  114.   | Sym x -> bprintf b "\t%s\t%s" s x
  115.   | _ -> assert false

  222. (* bug:
  223.    https://sourceware.org/binutils/docs-2.22/as/i386_002dBugs.html#i386_002dBugs

  225.    The AT&T syntax has a bug for fsub/fdiv/fsubr/fdivr instructions when
  226.    the source register is %st and the destination is %st(i).  In those
  227.    case, AT&T use fsub (resp. fsubr) in place of fsubr (resp. fsub),
  228.    and idem for fdiv/fdivr.

  230.    Concretely, AT&T syntax interpretation of:

  232.       fsub  %st, %st(3)

  234.    should normally be:

  236.       %st(3) := %st(3) - %st

  238.    but it should actually be interpreted as:

  240.       %st(3) := %st - %st(3)

  242.    which means the FSUBR instruction should be used.
  243. *)


  246. ‌let print_line b = function
  247.   | Ins instr -> print_instr b instr

  249.   | Align (_data,n) ->
  250.       (* MacOSX assembler interprets the integer n as a 2^n alignment *)
  251.       let n = if system = S_macosx then Misc.log2 n else n in
  252.       bprintf b "\t.align\t%d" n
  253.   | Byte n -> bprintf b "\t.byte\t%a" cst n
  254.   | Bytes s ->
  255.       if system = S_solaris then buf_bytes_directive b ".byte" s
  256.       else bprintf b "\t.ascii\t\"%s\"" (string_of_string_literal s)
  257.   | Comment s -> bprintf b "\t\t\t\t/* %s */" s
  258.   | Global s -> bprintf b "\t.globl\t%s" s;
  259.   | Long n -> bprintf b "\t.long\t%a" cst n
  260.   | NewLabel (s, _) -> bprintf b "%s:" s
  261.   | Quad n -> bprintf b "\t.quad\t%a" cst n
  262.   | Section ([".data" ], _, _) -> bprintf b "\t.data"
  263.   | Section ([".text" ], _, _) -> bprintf b "\t.text"
  264.   | Section (name, flags, args) ->
  265.       bprintf b "\t.section %s" (String.concat "," name);
  266.       begin match flags with
  267.       | None -> ()
  268.       | Some flags -> bprintf b ",%S" flags
  269.       end;
  270.       begin match args with
  271.       | [] -> ()
  272.       | _ -> bprintf b ",%s" (String.concat "," args)
  273.       end
  274.   | Space n ->
  275.       if system = S_solaris then bprintf b "\t.zero\t%d" n
  276.       else bprintf b "\t.space\t%d" n
  277.   | Word n ->
  278.       if system = S_solaris then bprintf b "\t.value\t%a" cst n
  279.       else bprintf b "\t.word\t%a" cst n

  281.   (* gas only *)
  282.   | Cfi_adjust_cfa_offset n -> bprintf b "\t.cfi_adjust_cfa_offset %d" n
  283.   | Cfi_endproc -> bprintf b "\t.cfi_endproc"
  284.   | Cfi_startproc -> bprintf b "\t.cfi_startproc"
  285.   | Cfi_remember_state -> bprintf b "\t.cfi_remember_state"
  286.   | Cfi_restore_state -> bprintf b "\t.cfi_restore_state"
  287.   | Cfi_def_cfa_register reg -> bprintf b "\t.cfi_def_cfa_register %%%s" reg
  288.   | Cfi_def_cfa_offset n -> bprintf b "\t.cfi_def_cfa_offset %d" n
  289.   | File (file_num, file_name) ->
  290.       bprintf b "\t.file\t%d\t\"%s\""
  291.         file_num (X86_proc.string_of_string_literal file_name)
  292.   | Indirect_symbol s -> bprintf b "\t.indirect_symbol %s" s
  293.   | Loc (file_num, line, col) ->
  294.       (* PR#7726: Location.none uses column -1, breaks LLVM assembler *)
  295.       if col >= 0 then bprintf b "\t.loc\t%d\t%d\t%d" file_num line col
  296.       else bprintf b "\t.loc\t%d\t%d" file_num line
  297.   | Private_extern s -> bprintf b "\t.private_extern %s" s
  298.   | Set (arg1, arg2) -> bprintf b "\t.set %s, %a" arg1 cst arg2
  299.   | Size (s, c) -> bprintf b "\t.size %s,%a" s cst c
  300.   | Type (s, typ) -> bprintf b "\t.type %s,%s" s typ

  302.   (* masm only *)
  303.   | External _
  304.   | Mode386
  305.   | Model _
  306.     -> assert false

  308. ‌let generate_asm oc lines =
  309.   let b = Buffer.create 10000 in
  310.   output_string oc "\t.file \"\"\n"; (* PR#7037 *)
  311.   List.iter
  312.     (fun i ->
  313.        Buffer.clear b;
  314.        print_line b i;
  315.        Buffer.add_char b '\n';
  316.        Buffer.output_buffer oc b;
  317.     )
  318.     lines
